---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="About"
  description="Ajmal Khan, Quality Engineering leader with 15 years across QA, test strategy, and AI systems testing. Writes TestEnigma."
  active="about"
>
  <div class="wrap about-wrap">
    <img class="avatar-lg" src="/images/profile.jpg" alt="Ajmal Khan" style="object-fit:cover" />
    <div class="about-body">
      <div class="eyebrow">About</div>
      <h1>Hi, I&#8217;m Ajmal Khan</h1>
      <p class="sub">Quality Engineering leader, 15 years across QA, test strategy, and now AI systems testing.</p>

      <div class="stat-row reveal">
        <div class="stat-item">
          <div class="stat-num" data-count="15" data-suffix="+">0</div>
          <div class="stat-label">Years in QA &amp; test strategy</div>
        </div>
        <div class="stat-item" style="--d:.08s">
          <div class="stat-num" data-count="100" data-suffix="+">0</div>
          <div class="stat-label">Peak deploys/day shipped</div>
        </div>
        <div class="stat-item stat-item-cadence" style="--d:.16s">
          <div class="cadence-row">
            <span>3-month cycles</span>
            <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.7" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M5 12h14M13 6l6 6-6 6"></path></svg>
            <span class="accent">100+/day</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stat-label">Release cadence, both ends</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p>I&#8217;ve spent 15 years in Quality Engineering across companies ranging from large MNCs to early-stage startups, which means I&#8217;ve worked both ends of the release-cadence spectrum: three-month release cycles where every change was a ceremony, and continuous deployment pipelines shipping 100+ changes to production in a day. That range is where most of what I actually know about test strategy comes from.</p>

      <div class="tabs reveal" role="tablist" aria-label="Focus areas">
        <button class="tab-btn on" data-tab="strategy">Test Strategy</button>
        <button class="tab-btn" data-tab="micro">Microservices &amp; APIs</button>
        <button class="tab-btn" data-tab="ai">AI &amp; LLM Testing</button>
      </div>
      <div class="tab-panel active" data-panel="strategy">
        <p>Test strategy is the discipline of turning &#8220;we shipped and nothing broke&#8221; from luck into a guarantee: deciding what actually needs coverage, at which layer, and what&#8217;s safe to leave untested. Fifteen years of doing that across both three-month release trains and 100-deploys-a-day pipelines is where most of what&#8217;s on this blog comes from.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="tab-panel" data-panel="micro">
        <p>Contract tests at the API boundary, integration tests where services actually talk to each other, and knowing which of the two catches a given class of bug. Most production incidents I&#8217;ve debugged trace back to a boundary nobody tested, not a unit that was undertested.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="tab-panel" data-panel="ai">
        <p>The newest focus: applying that same discipline (know what you&#8217;re actually verifying, test at the right layer, don&#8217;t trust a green check you can&#8217;t explain) to systems where the thing under test doesn&#8217;t return the same answer twice. Currently formalizing it through a degree in AI Engineering and MLOps at BITS Pilani. TestEnigma is where it gets written up.</p>
      </div>

      <p>Outside of work, I&#8217;m in the gym more often than not. Same principle as testing, honestly: consistency beats intensity.</p>
      <p>Have feedback, a correction, or an idea for a post? Reach out on LinkedIn, or leave a comment on any post here.</p>
      <div class="pill-row">
        <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/ajmal-khan-98254871/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
          <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="currentColor" style="width:16px;height:16px"><path d="M20.45 20.45h-3.55v-5.57c0-1.33-.02-3.04-1.85-3.04-1.86 0-2.14 1.45-2.14 2.94v5.67H9.36V9h3.41v1.56h.05c.47-.9 1.63-1.85 3.36-1.85 3.6 0 4.27 2.37 4.27 5.45zM5.34 7.43a2.06 2.06 0 1 1 0-4.12 2.06 2.06 0 0 1 0 4.12zM7.11 20.45H3.56V9h3.55z"></path></svg>
          linkedin.com/in/ajmal-khan
        </a>
        <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="https://github.com/ajmalkhan92" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
          <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="currentColor" style="width:16px;height:16px"><path d="M12 .5C5.65.5.5 5.65.5 12c0 5.08 3.29 9.39 7.86 10.91.58.11.79-.25.79-.56 0-.27-.01-1.17-.02-2.12-3.2.7-3.88-1.36-3.88-1.36-.52-1.33-1.28-1.68-1.28-1.68-1.04-.71.08-.7.08-.7 1.15.08 1.76 1.19 1.76 1.19 1.03 1.75 2.69 1.25 3.35.95.1-.74.4-1.25.72-1.54-2.55-.29-5.24-1.28-5.24-5.68 0-1.26.45-2.28 1.19-3.09-.12-.29-.52-1.46.11-3.05 0 0 .97-.31 3.18 1.18a11.1 11.1 0 0 1 5.8 0c2.2-1.49 3.17-1.18 3.17-1.18.63 1.59.23 2.76.11 3.05.74.81 1.19 1.83 1.19 3.09 0 4.41-2.69 5.38-5.25 5.67.41.35.77 1.05.77 2.12 0 1.53-.01 2.76-.01 3.14 0 .3.21.67.8.55A11.5 11.5 0 0 0 23.5 12C23.5 5.65 18.35.5 12 .5z"></path></svg>
          github.com/ajmalkhan92
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<script>
  const tabBtns = document.querySelectorAll('.about-body .tab-btn');
  tabBtns.forEach((btn) => {
    btn.addEventListener('click', () => {
      tabBtns.forEach((b) => b.classList.remove('on'));
      btn.classList.add('on');
      document.querySelectorAll('.about-body .tab-panel').forEach((p) => p.classList.remove('active'));
      const tab = (btn as HTMLElement).dataset.tab;
      document.querySelector(`.about-body .tab-panel[data-panel="${tab}"]`)?.classList.add('active');
    });
  });

  const reduced = window.matchMedia('(prefers-reduced-motion: reduce)').matches;
  const counters = document.querySelectorAll<HTMLElement>('.stat-num');
  const animateCount = (el: HTMLElement) => {
    const target = Number(el.dataset.count || 0);
    const suffix = el.dataset.suffix || '';
    if (reduced) { el.textContent = target + suffix; return; }
    const duration = 900;
    const start = performance.now();
    const tick = (now: number) => {
      const t = Math.min((now - start) / duration, 1);
      const eased = 1 - Math.pow(1 - t, 3);
      el.textContent = Math.round(eased * target) + suffix;
      if (t < 1) requestAnimationFrame(tick);
    };
    requestAnimationFrame(tick);
  };
  if ('IntersectionObserver' in window && counters.length) {
    const io = new IntersectionObserver((entries) => {
      entries.forEach((en) => {
        if (en.isIntersecting) { animateCount(en.target as HTMLElement); io.unobserve(en.target); }
      });
    }, { threshold: 0.4 });
    counters.forEach((el) => io.observe(el));
  } else {
    counters.forEach((el) => animateCount(el));
  }
</script>
